description:
Through guided discovery and problem solving, participants will have the opportunity to explore and experiment with a wide variety of paper sculpture techniques. Facilitated by artist Carol Knowlton-Dority, each participant will choose and use paper sculpture techniques to create his/her own expressive piece of art. All materials will be provided. This workshop is open to participants of all ages!

About the FacilitatorCarol Knowlton-Dority's artistic vision brings together contemporary visual art with meditative practice in order to consider the relationship between reflection and transformation. Carol has exhibited her works at various art galleries across Toronto. You can find more about her work on her website, on Facebook, and on Twitter.
title: SA Creates: Expressive Arts – Exploring Paper Sculpture Workshop

description:
BACK FROM SHORE LEAVE! A RESCHEDULED SCREENING OF ON THE TOWN!

Follow three sailors (Gene Kelly, Frank Sinatra, and Jules Munshin) on shore leave in New York, New York in one of the greatest musicals of all time, the MGM spectacular, On the Town! The 1949 musical reunites Singin’ in the Rain directors Kelley and Stanley Donen, and features music by Leonard Bernstein (West Side Story), who wrote the original score for the stage, and Roger Edens (A Star Is Born). On the Town also stars Vera-Ellen, Betty Garrett, and Ann Miller, and won the Academy Award for Best Music. Join Musicale on March 19 for the highly anticipated milestone: our first Gene Kelly movie—and our second Frank Sinatra!

MUSICALE – (noun) a program of music performed at a party – is a monthly film series at The Royal that celebrates everything from 1950s musicals to hip hop documentaries!

description: Rodgers + Hammerstein's CINDARELLA is the Tony Award-winning Broadway musical from the creators of The Sound of Music and South Pacific that's delighting audiences with its contemporary take on the classic tale. This lush production features an incredible orchestra, jaw-dropping transformations and all the moments you love-the pumpkin, the glass slipper, the masked ball and more-plus some surprising new twists! Be transported back to your childhood as you rediscover some of Rogers + Hammerstein's most beloved songs, including "In My Own Little Corner", "Impossible/It's Possible" and "Ten Minutes Ago", in this hilarious and romantic Broadway experience for anyone who's ever had a wish, a dream...or a really great pair of shoes. Running time: 2 hours and 15 minutes including intermission. Age Appropriateness: Family

description: BrickCan is back - For LEGO fans of all ages! Canada's largest Public LEGO Exhibition returns to the River Rock in Richmond! Choose your preferred viewing day and time - morning, mid-day, or afternoon, and plan to spend a few hours. Your ticket gives you 2 hours of time in the giant display hall, entry into "Creation Station", with thousands of bricks to build and play with (between 9am and 4pm), and access to "Vendor Alley", with classic or custom sets, unique accessories, artwork, jewellery, T-shirts, and more available to buy. Children 3 and younger do not need a ticket. Ticketholders 12 and under receive an exclusive BrickCan LEGO kit to take home! For a great overnight adventure, book a room right at the fabulous River Rock Resort! Discounted rates are available for BrickCan guests for a limited time. Book through the BrickCan website. Strollers and wagons are not be permitted at BrickCan due to space restrictions. The event is fully wheelchair accessible.
